handNote.desc:
Fine and trained hand. Characters are regularly spaced.
The script displays some relatively archaic features: the numeral ፮ has a compressed shape and the open loop;
the letter መ has the loops not completely separated; the letter ዐ and numeral ፬ show "cone-forms" (for the letter ፀ, this is much less 
salient); the letter ኍ has the vowel marker on the top of the letter body; 
however, the word እግዚአ፡ ብሔር፡ is written as one word.
